{
  "_meta": {
    "description": "Mapping table from Unicode codepoints (Arabic) to cp1256 single-byte values for ESC/POS printing on Datecs DPP-250.",
    "encoding": "windows-1256",
    "notes": [
      "cp1256 covers U+0621..U+064A (Arabic block) + U+0651..U+0652 (shadda/sukun) + a few presentation forms.",
      "cp1256 has only ISOLATED letter forms. For joined display you must shape on the JS side first (use arabicReshape() in cp1256.ts), then map each shaped codepoint via this table.",
      "ASCII (0x00-0x7F) maps 1:1 — not duplicated here.",
      "Latin-1 punctuation (space, digits 0-9, comma, dot, colon, semicolon, parentheses, dash) maps 1:1.",
      "Western digits (0-9, 0x30-0x39) and Arabic-Indic digits (U+0660-U+0669, mapped to 0xF0-0xF9 in cp1256)."
    ]
  },
